properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 5 at 4:08AM PST until January 6 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning above 3000 feet, heavy snow
expected. Total snow accumulations of 8 to 16 inches. For the
Winter Weather Advisory above 2000 feet, snow expected. Total
snow accumulations of 4 to 10 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 4 AM to 4 PM PST
Monday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, from 10 AM this
morning to 4 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to near impossible.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
